This head, with its remarkably broad brow and cheekbones, its handsome, sensual mouth, and its cold, majes- tic expression, was not disfigured by the ap- proach of death. It was the same as Pierre re- membered it three months before, when the count had sent him to Petersburg. But now this head was swaying helplessly with the uneven movements of the bearers, and the cold listless gaze fixed itself upon nothing.
